Hey <@U030ZNR7QUU>,
it seems like the CSS part is a bit off.
If you write it like it is right now
```h2, p, h3 {
    font-family: arial;
    color: {{brand_settings.accentColor1.hex}};
}
header {
    padding: 10px 6%;
    background: {{brand_settings.primaryColor.hex}};
    margin-bottom: 0;
    color: {{theme.header_text_color.color }};
}
footer {
  background: {{brand_settings.secondaryColor.hex}};
  padding: 20px 6%;
  margin-top: 5%;
}```
the settings from the theme settings won't be applied.

If you like to have the theme values being applied it should look like this:
```h2, p, h3 {
    font-family: arial;
    color: {{theme.accent_branding_body_text_color.css}};
}
header {
    padding: 10px 6%;
    background: {{theme.primary_branding_color.css}};
    margin-bottom: 0;
    color: {{theme.header_text_color.color }};
}
footer {
  background: {{theme.secondaryColor.css}};
  padding: 20px 6%;
  margin-top: 5%;
}```
also: with colors you have a few options to render.
.color will provide the color(hex) value
.opacity will provide the opactiy(if there's one)
.css will render the color as hex or rgb(if you set a different opacity than "100")

also - in order to remove the opacity option from the color field, add this to each color field you don't want to have opacity:
```"visibility": {
					"hidden_subfields": {
						"opacity": true
					}
				},```
So the whole color field looks like this:
```{
				"name": "primary",
				"alternate_names": ["primary_color"],
				"label": "Primary color",
				"required": false,
				"locked": false,
				"inline_help_text": "",
				"help_text": "",
				"type": "color",
				"inherited_value": {
					"property_value_paths": {
						"color": "brand_settings.primaryColor"
					}
				},
				"visibility": {
					"hidden_subfields": {
						"opacity": true
					}
				},
				"default": {
					"color": "#A8EB12"
				}
			}```
